sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: nahR (Pseudomonas putida, see BBa_K1031610) is expressed under the constitutive Pr promoter. It encodes a regulatory protein that activates the Psal promoter (see BBa_J61051) in the presence of salicylate. yhjH (see BBa_K1973034) is expressed from the Psal promoter in the presence of this molecule. nasF (see BBa_K1973001) is an attenuator of transcription elongation (terminator) from Klebsiella pneumoniae that decreases the basal expression from the Psal promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alvaro Escobar Doncel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We digested BBa_K1973034 as a vector (EcoRI and XbaI) and BBa_K1973005 as an insert (EcoRI and SpeI), and then we ligate them.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: nasF is an attenuator of transcription elongation (terminator) from Klebsiella pneumoniae that decreases the basal expression from the Psal promoter. The nasR protein disrupts the terminator structure and allows the expression again, providing an useful tool for tight ON/OFF expression systems.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: yhjH encodes the YhjH protein, a c-diGMP (cyclic diguanilate monophosphate) phosphodiesterase. c-diGMP regulates both the formation and dispersion of the biofilm, depending on the quantity of it that is present inside the cell. High levels of c-diGMP will increase the biofilm formation, and low levels of it will induce its dispersion. To manipulate this, we will make use of a phosphodiesterase, that will destroy the c-diGMP, and a diguanilate cyclase, that will produce it, YhjH and PleD* respectively.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We have inlcuded the sequence of RBS BBa_B0034 by means of the PCR primers used for the amplification, as well as the scar it should have been in case of the clonation of this part.
